@page "/about"
@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authorization
@attribute [AllowAnonymous]

<div class="card">
    <h2>About</h2>
    <p><strong>Ethan Townsend's Social Site</strong> — Cohort 39.</p>
    <p>Welcome to Ethan Townsend's Social Site, a Blazor Server-based social profile demo designed to showcase the power of modern web development with .NET 8.</p>

    <h3>Purpose</h3>
    <p>This site was created as part of Cohort 39 to demonstrate the capabilities of Blazor Server for building interactive, real-time web applications. It provides a platform for users to create and manage their profiles, interact with others, and explore the features of a modern social media application.</p>

    <h3>Features</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>User Profiles:</strong> Create and customize your personal profile with details like your photo, bio, age, likes, and favorite food.</li>
        <li><strong>Photo Sharing:</strong> Upload and view photos on your profile or other users' profiles.</li>
        <li><strong>Messaging:</strong> Leave messages on other users' profiles and view messages left on your own profile.</li>
        <li><strong>Search:</strong> Find other users using the user search feature.</li>
        <li><strong>Admin Tools:</strong> Manage roles and users (if you have admin privileges).</li>
        <li><strong>Authentication:</strong> Secure login and registration using ASP.NET Identity.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Technologies Used</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Blazor Server:</strong> For building interactive and dynamic web pages.</li>
        <li><strong>.NET 8:</strong> The latest version of the .NET framework for high-performance backend logic.</li>
        <li><strong>Entity Framework Core:</strong> For database access and management.</li>
        <li><strong>ASP.NET Identity:</strong> For user authentication and authorization.</li>
        <li><strong>CSS:</strong> Custom styles for a modern and responsive design.</li>
    </ul>


    <h3>Contact</h3>
    <p>If you have any questions, feedback, or suggestions, feel free to reach out to Ethan Townsend at ethantownsend.dev.</p>
</div>